Vice President Kamala Harris visited the SMART Training Facility in Boston, Massachusetts to discuss the importance of labor and worker training. She praised the work of Shamaiah, a representative of Local 17, and expressed her admiration for Senator Ed Markey and Representative Ayanna Pressley. Harris also recognized Mayor Wu for her leadership on worker empowerment and childcare. She highlighted the administration's efforts to create good-paying, union jobs, protect workers' rights, and lower costs for American families. The Vice President mentioned initiatives such as capping insulin prescription costs, allowing Medicare to negotiate drug prices, and providing tax cuts for parents. She also emphasized the cancellation of student loan debt and the investment in home energy efficiency, which would help lower energy bills and create jobs. Harris concluded by expressing pride in the work being done and the positive impact it will have on the nation's strength, prosperity, and global leadership.